.13743444,0.01803180,0.03986250,-0.03335170,0.00501858,-0.07569832,0.08854396,0.07870339,0.01851879,0.04145805,0.07652033,-0.01228249,0.01117458,0.02496966,-0.04566227,0.03823541,-0.00995803,0.02401048,0.00152404,0.00857726,-0.00864014,0.02532576,0.02163135,-0.05006183,-0.09090494,-0.06302730,-0.04062052,-0.01098048,-0.04523863,0.00827978,0.00451914,-0.00165586,0.03968440,-0.04795366,0.03337814,-0.02753088,0.00466263,0.01634239,0.02128005,-0.02578333,0.06978329,0.01725700,0.00434303]',E'pgx - PostgreSQL Driver and Toolkit\n\npgx is a pure Go driver and toolkit for PostgreSQL.\n\nThe pgx driver is a low-level, high performance interface that exposes PostgreSQL-specific features such as `LISTEN` /\n`NOTIFY` and `COPY`. It also includes an adapter for the standard `database/sql` interface.\n\nThe toolkit component is a related set of packages that implement PostgreSQL functionality such as parsing the wire protocol\nand type mapping between PostgreSQL and Go. These underlying packages can be used to implement alternative drivers,\nproxies, load balancers, logical replication clients, etc.','{"source": "postgresql", "version": "17", "language": "go", "title": "pgx - PostgreSQL Driver and Toolkit", "section_title": "README", "url": "https://github.com/jackc/pgx/blob/master/README.md", "topics": "postgresql,pgx,go,sql,README", "categories": "database,sql,go"}');
