38,0.13189001,0.06611601,0.03362730,-0.03234933,0.02008775,-0.01787128,0.03182788,0.05381342,0.00156304,-0.00504454,0.03286902,-0.04737381,-0.01076787,0.02157687,0.00281353,0.04133781,0.02599732,-0.03299153,-0.01796393,0.02614472,-0.03360133,0.00337882,0.02923687,-0.01291852,-0.05559988,-0.03684933,-0.01565169,0.01000745,-0.04600245,-0.01220345,0.03783885,-0.00784083,0.05065220,-0.02960281,0.03290366,0.04655799,0.03304175,0.04042860,0.11994708,-0.01230383,0.01754741,0.04137792,-0.01941551]',E'Choosing Between the pgx and database/sql Interfaces\n\nThe pgx interface is faster. Many PostgreSQL specific features such as `LISTEN` / `NOTIFY` and `COPY` are not available\nthrough the `database/sql` interface.\n\nThe pgx interface is recommended when:\n\n1. The application only targets PostgreSQL.\n2. No other libraries that require `database/sql` are in use.\n\nIt is also possible to use the `database/sql` interface and convert a connection to the lower-level pgx interface as needed.','{"source": "postgresql", "version": "17", "language": "go", "title": "pgx - PostgreSQL Driver and Toolkit", "section_title": "README", "url": "https://github.com/jackc/pgx/blob/master/README.md", "topics": "postgresql,pgx,go,sql,README", "categories": "database,sql,go"}');
